Swaziland Cabinet Ministers Agree to 10% Salary Cut, Business Report Says

-- B y   G o r d o n   B e l l
-- 
2011-03-25T05:44:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-25/swaziland-cabinet-ministers-agree-to-10-salary-cut-business-report-says.html
Swaziland’s cabinet ministers
agreed to a 10 percent cut in their salaries to show the
government is committed to meeting financial lenders’ demands to
reduce the state wage bill, Business Report said, citing Prime
Minister Barnabas Sibusiso.  Civil servants are opposed to having their wages cut, the
Johannesburg-based newspaper reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  